During the summit of the two leaders last month, Kim told Moon he wanted to invite the pope to North Korea, the spokesman added. SEOUL – North Korean leader Kim Jong Un has invited Pope Francis to Pyongyang, South Korea’s presidential Blue House said on Tuesday. South Korean President Moon Jae-in will deliver Kim’s invitation when he meets Francis next week during his trip to Europe, Blue House spokesperson Kim Eui-kyeom told a news briefing. During the summit of the two leaders last month, Kim told Moon he wanted to invite the pope to North Korea, the spokesperson added.